title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland Auditorium Arena on 1981-12-27
lineage: Master Cassettes (Dolby B)(Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz)> dBpoweramp 2496 > Adobe Audition 3.01 > TLH flac2496
description:
Set I
Minglewood Blues-> Sugaree, Cassidy, Deep Elem Blues->CC Rider, Friend Of The Devil, Passenger, Althea ->Looks Like Rain->Deal
Set II
Samson & Delilah, To Lay Me Down-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Playin' In The Band-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: It's All Over Now Baby Blue

reviews.review_text: Best Wheel Ever This was an amazing show, I saw this whole run and was in shock after this one.  (until NYE, then i was REALLY in shock)  The whole show is beautiful but after the drums is pure magic.  The Wheel just carries you away.  Wonderful recording.  The only thing it can't capture was the feeling inside the building, very psychedelic and communal feel.  God bless the mighty Grateful Dead.

NYE Run '81: N2 Final Passenger. End of an era. This whole run feels very transitional to me: So long, early '80s. The closing first set triptych (Althea -> LLR -> Deal) rips. Playin' sandwich pleases.
